description:
Speaker: Brett Cannon

Burn-out is common in open source due to a misunderstanding of what users, contributors, and maintainers should expect from each other. This talk will set out to help everyone set reasonable expectations of each other in order to make open source pleasant for everyone involved.

From PyCascades 2018 in Vancouver, BC, Canada

Recorded by: Elaine at http://jollygoodrecordings.ca
title: Brett Cannon Setting Expectations for Open Source Participation
